This paper discusses a framework for mining high-utility sequential patterns, which involves analyzing data and identifying patterns. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including databases (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). However, since the paper focuses on mining patterns across multiple sequences, cs.DB and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories.
